com.guidewire.util.webservices
Interface GWSOAPOperation

Deprecated. Use APILocator.getAuthenticatedProxy(Class, String, String, String) 

public interface GWSOAPOperation

An interface that represents a SOAP operation to run. An operation should be a discrete chunk of code that performs a single SOAP action, not necessarily one soap call.
An operation can use mulltiple API interfaces from multiple hosts. Use the method getProxy off of the provider to get a handle to an authenticated proxy.
Proxy objects returned by getProxy are pooled. This is done to save the overhead of creating and authenticating the proxy.
Upon completion of the operation, the proxy used by the operation are returned to the pool.

run

java.lang.Object run(GWSOAPProvider provider)
                     throws java.lang.Exception
Deprecated. Use APILocator.getAuthenticatedProxy(Class, String, String, String)

Runs the given operation. Implementations of this interface should override this method to perform all work to be done by the operation. WARNING: Do not return a proxy or the provider from this method. Doing so will result in an error.

Parameters:
provider - Utility class that provides proxies and such for this operation.
Returns:
This method can return any value it likes. The return value will be the return value of APILocator.executeSOAPOperation
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
